Issue #72 — browser-side lesson packages probe log
=====================================================

Fixture: /tmp/bt-fixture-72
  - blendtutor.toml: single lesson "pandas-import" -> add.yaml
  - add.yaml: language Python, packages: [pandas], checks import pandas

Build:
  cargo run -p blendtutor-cli -- build /tmp/bt-fixture-72 --target pyodide -o /tmp/bt-vision-72
  -> exited 0, lessons/0.json contains "packages": ["pandas"]

Serve:
  python3 /tmp/serve_headers.py on port 8889 with COOP/COEP headers
  -> http://localhost:8889/ reachable

Rodney probes:

1. window.__bt.lessons[0].packages includes "pandas"
   Command: uvx rodney assert "window.__bt && window.__bt.lessons.length > 0 && window.__bt.lessons[0].packages.includes('pandas')"
   Result: PASS

2. Boot completes (run button enabled)
   Command: uvx rodney assert "document.querySelector('#run').disabled === false"
   Result: PASS

3. Lesson runs and reaches pass status
   Action: uvx rodney click "#run"
   Wait loop: uvx rodney assert "document.querySelector('[data-test=lesson-status]').dataset.status === 'pass'"
   Result: PASS
   Output text: "All checks passed."

Screenshots:
  - docs/evidence/72/lesson-loaded.png : lesson picker loaded, run button enabled
  - docs/evidence/72/lesson-pass.png  : status data-status="pass", output "All checks passed."

Notes:
  - The Pyodide adapter calls pyodide.loadPackage(packages) before evaluation
    (crates/core/assets/pyodide/lesson-runner.js). The pass on a lesson whose
    only third-party dependency is pandas confirms the package was loaded.
  - loadPackage itself is module-local and not directly observable from the
    page global scope, so the call is verified indirectly by the passing run.
